frameDefinitions: This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
A Speaker communicates a message stating an Item's membership in a Category, i.e., asserts that the Item has the defining characteristics of the Category.
This frame concerns a specific subset of Instances of a Type which are evaluated in terms of their similarity to a conceptual prototype of the Type.
A Shopper looks for Goods in order to purchase them.
A Questioner asks a Witness (or defendant) questions in the context of a court procedure.
One linguistic unit, Sign_1, has a relation to another linguistic unit, Sign_2.
frameExamples: I don't like this newfangled <t><fex name='Subtype'>kind</fex></t> of  fish.
He <t>depicted</t> his involvement as merely peripheral.
We 'd like to <t>cross-examine</t> the witness if we can.
listRoleDefinitions: The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
The individual that communicates the message concerning the <fen>Category</fen> of an <fen>Item</fen>.
The class of entities with characteristics that match those of the <fen>Item</fen> according to the portrayal of the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The entity that the <fen>Speaker</fen> portrays as belonging to a <fen>Category</fen>.
The piece of text in which a <fen>Speaker</fen> communicates their categorization of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The point in time at which the <fen>Speaker</fen> makes a characterization of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Speaker</fen> characterizes the <fen>Item</fen>
A thing or episode that is considered exemplary of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of things or events from which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
The person who attempts to find the <fen>Goods</fen>.
This is the entity that the Ground may contain. Typically, it is expressed as a<ment>for</ment>-PP.
This role identifies the time when the shopping occurs.
A spatial setting larger than the Ground in which the Shopping event occurs.
The individual who asks a <fen>Witness</fen> questions.
A person who is present in a courtroom in order to give some form of evidence, has been sworn in, and is being examined by a <fen>Questioner</fen>.
When the examination occurs.
Where the examination takes place.
